# Local SEO Auditor

## Source of truth

Before implementing, read the relevant doc:

| Doc | Use when |
|-----|----------|
| `docs/SPEC.md` | Product behavior, URL/sitemap/crawl rules |
| `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` | Stack, types, API, file structure |
| `docs/CHECKS.md` | SEO check rules and severities |
| `docs/UI.md` | Components and layout |
| `docs/TASKS.md` | Current phase — implement one phase at a time |
| `docs/ACCEPTANCE.md` | Definition of done |

## Workflow

1. Check `docs/TASKS.md` for the next unchecked phase.
2. Implement only that phase.
3. Ensure TypeScript compiles.
4. Mark tasks complete in `docs/TASKS.md`.
5. Do not skip ahead or implement everything in one file.

## Hard constraints

- Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind
- No database, auth, Playwright, AI APIs, or paid external services
- Analyze raw server-rendered HTML only
- Canonicals must match the audited environment (localhost ≠ production)
- Default concurrency: 5 · timeout: 15s · User-Agent: `local-seo-auditor/1.0`
- One check per file under `lib/audit/checks/`
- Prioritize audit logic correctness over visual polish

## Stack dependencies only

`cheerio`, `fast-xml-parser`, `zod`, `p-limit` — no unnecessary packages.
